11/07/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- The Greek government has expressed gratitude for the help Albania has provided over the years, according to local media reports Friday (9 July). During a meeting with Albanian President Alfred Moisiu, Greek Defence Minister Spilios Spiliotopoulos said Athens is grateful to Albania for its past support, especially during WWII. Spiliotopoulos reportedly stressed that the current solid bilateral relations are based on this old friendship.
In other news, Albanian Foreign Minister Kastriot Islami wrapped up a two-day visit to Paris on Friday. He called on the government to provide more incentives for French businesses to invest in Albania. He stressed opportunities for investment in strategic sectors, given the process of privatisation. (Albanian Daily News - 10/07/04)
